ical component. Place of service is not explicitly documented, but the presence of a formal radiology report with professional signature supports modifier 26 use per radiology specialty rules.\\n\\n3. Documentation quality: Adequate for coding purposes. The indication, technique, and findings are clearly stated. No overcoding risk; the single-view code matches the documented technique exactly.", "stage": "3_coding", "title": "Code Candidate Generation", "samples": 1, "candidates": [{"code": "R10.9", "role": "primary", "sequence": 1, "modifiers": [], "_agreement": 1.0, "confidence": 0.95, "code_system": "ICD10CM", "description": "Unspecified abdominal pain", "chart_citations": [{"text": "Abdominal pain.", "section": "HISTORY", "line_end": 3, "line_start": 3}], "rule_justification": "Abdominal pain is the documented indication for the study; no definitive diagnosis was established, so the symptom is coded per ICD-10-CM guidelines.", "guideline_citations": [{"text": "When no definitive diagnosis is documented, code the sign or symptom that prompted the encounter or study.", "source": "ICD-10-CM Official Guidelines", "section": "Signs and Symptoms"}]}, {"code": "74018", "role": "procedure", "sequence": 1, "modifiers": ["26"], "_agreement": 1.0, "confidence": 0.98, "code_system": "CPT", "description": "Radiologic exam, abdomen; single view", "chart_citations": [{"text": "Abdomen X-ray, single view", "section": "EXAM", "line_end": 2, "line_start": 2}, {"text": "Single supine view of the abdomen.", "section": "TECHNIQUE", "line_end": 4, "line_start": 4}], "rule_justification": "Single-view abdominal X-ray documented; modifier 26 appended for professional component (radiologist interpretation) per radiology specialty rules.", "guideline_citations": [{"text": "Select the CPT that matches the documented number of views (e.g., single vs 2-view chest; 3-view vs 4+-view knee). Do not bill a higher view-count code than documented.", "source": "Radiology Coding Guidance", "section