ent, permanent) so the unspecified code is appropriate. (2) Palpitations (R00.2) is coded as secondary diagnosis representing the presenting symptom that led to the ECG. Per ICD-10-CM guidelines, symptoms may be coded in addition to a related definitive diagnosis when they represent the reason for the encounter. (3) CPT 93000 is assigned for the complete 12-lead ECG service including interpretation and report. No modifier 26 is appended because the chart does not specify this was performed at a facility (POS 22/23) with only professional component billing; the global code is appropriate when place of service is unclear. (4) The report is properly signed by the cardiologist (line 6), meeting documentation requirements. (5) No overcoding risk: avoided assigning more specific atrial fibrillation codes (I48.0, I48.1, I48.2) that would require documentation of type/pattern not present in this chart.", "stage": "3_coding", "title": "Code Candidate Generation", "samples": 1, "candidates": [{"code": "I48.91", "role": "principal", "sequence": 1, "modifiers": [], "_agreement": 1.0, "confidence": 0.95, "code_system": "ICD10CM", "description": "Unspecified atrial fibrillation", "chart_citations": [{"text": "IMPRESSION: Atrial fibrillation.", "section": "IMPRESSION", "line_end": 5, "line_start": 5}, {"text": "FINDINGS: Irregularly irregular rhythm, absent P waves, fibrillatory baseline, ventricular rate 88 bpm; no acute ST changes.", "section": "FINDINGS", "line_end": 4, "line_start": 4}], "rule_justification": "Atrial fibrillation is the definitive diagnosis confirmed by ECG findings (irregularly irregular rhythm, absent P waves, fibrillatory baseline) and explicitly stated in the impression.", "guideline_citations": [{"text": "Code the cardiac diagnosis/indication (e.g., heart failure, valvular disease, arrhythmia); use a sign/symptom when no definitive diagnosis is established.", "source": "Cardiology Coding Guidance", "section": "Procedures"}]}, {"code": "R00.2", "role": "se