 than documented.", "source": "Radiology Coding Guidance", "section": "Views"}, {"text": "Report the most extensive endoscopic service performed in a session: colonoscopy with snare polypectomy = 45385; colonoscopy with biopsy = 45380; diagnostic colonoscopy = 45378; EGD with biopsy = 43239; diagnostic EGD = 43235. Do NOT separately report the diagnostic scope (45378/43235) when a therapeutic procedure is done in the same session. Code the finding (e.g., colon polyp K63.5, gastritis K29.70); for a screening colonoscopy that finds a polyp, sequence the screening Z-code first.", "source": "GI Endoscopy Coding Guidance", "section": "Procedures"}]}, {"hard": false, "notes": "Documentation is complete and unambiguous. The clinical diagnosis of actinic keratosis was made without biopsy, so the definitive diagnosis code L57.0 is appropriate. The procedure note explicitly states 'first lesion' and describes cryotherapy destruction of a single premalignant lesion, which directly supports CPT 17000. No bundling issues, no additional lesions documented, and no modifiers required. Medicare medical necessity is met (covered diagnosis L57 for CPT 17000). No overcoding risk; all codes are fully supported by documentation.", "stage": "3_coding", "title": "Code Candidate Generation", "samples": 1, "candidates": [{"code": "L57.0", "role": "primary", "sequence": 1, "modifiers": [], "_agreement": 1.0, "confidence": 1.0, "code_system": "ICD10CM", "description": "Actinic keratosis", "chart_citations": [{"text": "Scaly lesion on the forearm, clinically consistent with actinic keratosis.", "section": "INDICATION", "line_end": 2, "line_start": 2}, {"text": "Actinic keratosis destroyed by cryotherapy.", "section": "IMPRESSION", "line_end": 4, "line_start": 4}], "rule_justification": "Clinically diagnosed actinic keratosis confirmed in indication and impression; no biopsy performed, so definitive diagnosis code L57.0 is appropriate.", "guideline_citations": [{"text": "Code the lesion diagnosi