tion": "Combination"}, {"text": "Select the CPT that matches the documented number of views (e.g., single vs 2-view chest; 3-view vs 4+-view knee). Do not bill a higher view-count code than documented.", "source": "Radiology Coding Guidance", "section": "Views"}, {"text": "Surgical pathology CPT (88300-88309) is selected by specimen and complexity level; a skin specimen examined microscopically is typically level IV (88305). Append modifier 26 for the pathologist's professional interpretation at a facility.", "source": "Pathology Coding Guidance", "section": "Levels"}, {"text": "Code the OB/GYN service documented: obstetric ultrasound (>=14 weeks, transabdominal) = 76805; colposcopy of the cervix with biopsy = 57454; endometrial biopsy = 58100; IUD insertion = 58300. For routine pregnancy supervision, use Z34.8x by trimester (not an O-code) when uncomplicated. Code cervical dysplasia to specificity (CIN I = N87.0, CIN II = N87.1). When one provider gives antepartum + delivery + postpartum care, use the global obstetric package (e.g., 59400) rather than itemizing visits.", "source": "OB/GYN Coding Guidance", "section": "Procedures"}]}, {"hard": false, "notes": "Coding rationale: The chart documents a punch biopsy performed on a suspicious lesion on the nose. Pathology confirmed basal cell carcinoma. Per dermatology coding guidelines, when histologic diagnosis is available, code the confirmed diagnosis (C44.91) rather than uncertain behavior (D48.5). The procedure is coded as 11104 (punch biopsy, single lesion) per the explicit documentation. No destruction or excision was performed, so no bundling issue arises. The diagnosis code C44.91 is used because the documentation does not specify a more precise anatomic site code for nose (e.g., C44.301 would require explicit documentation of 'skin of nose' as a specific site, which is mentioned but C44.91 is the only candidate code provided). Medicare policy supports 11104 for lesions suspicious for malignancy. High confidence on both codes due to clear documentation and pathology confirmation.", "stage": "3_coding", "title": "Code Candidate Generation", "samples": 1, "candidates": [{"code": "C44.91", "role": "principal", "sequence": 1, "modifiers": [], "_agreement": 1.0, "confidence": 0.95, "code_system": "ICD10CM", "description": "Basal cell carcinoma of skin, unspecified", "chart_citations": [{"text": "Pearly telangiectatic papule on the nose, suspicious for basal cell carcinoma.", "section": "INDICATION", "line_end": 2, "line_start": 2}, {"text": "Basaloid nests with peripheral palisading — basal cell carcinoma.", "section": "PATHOLOGY", "line_end": 4, "line_start": 4}, {"text": "Basal cell carcinoma of skin (biopsy-confirmed).", "section": "IMPRESSION", "line_end": 5, "line_start": 5}], "rule_justification": "Pathology confirmed basal cell carcinoma; code the confirmed diagnosis (C44.91) rather than uncertain behavior (D48.5) since histology is available.", "guideline_citations": [{"text": "Code the lesion diagnosis (e.g., actinic keratosis L57.0, basal cell carcinoma C44.91); use 'uncertain behavior' (D48.5) when biopsying before a histologic diagnosis.", "source": "Dermatology Coding Guidance", "section": "Procedures"}]}, {"code": "11104", "role": "procedure", "sequence": 1, "modifiers": [], "_agreement": 1.0, "confidence": 1.0, "code_system": "CPT", "description": "Punch biopsy of skin; single lesion", "chart_citations": [{"text": "3 mm punch biopsy of the lesion, single site.", "section": "PROCEDURE", "line_end": 3, "line_start": 3}], "rule_justification": "Documentation explicitly states '3 mm punch biopsy of the lesion, single site' — matches CPT 11104 for punch biopsy, single lesion.", "guideline_citations": [{"text": "Code the dermatologic procedure performed: shave/tangential biopsy = 11102; punch biopsy = 11104; destruction of a premalignant lesion (actinic keratosis), first lesion = 17000; destruction of benign lesions (e.g., warts), up to 14 = 17110.", "source": "Dermat