yles and tibial plateau,\\" which matches the CPT 27447 descriptor for total knee arthroplasty. Laterality (right) is documented throughout, supporting the RT modifier. No unbundling attempted; anesthesia (01402) is separately billable by the anesthesia provider and not coded here per orthopedic specialty scope. No overcoding risks identified.", "stage": "3_coding", "title": "Code Candidate Generation", "samples": 1, "candidates": [{"code": "M17.11", "role": "principal", "sequence": 1, "modifiers": [], "_agreement": 1.0, "confidence": 1.0, "code_system": "ICD10CM", "description": "Unilateral primary osteoarthritis, right knee", "chart_citations": [{"text": "Severe primary osteoarthritis, right knee.", "section": "PREOPERATIVE DIAGNOSIS", "line_end": 2, "line_start": 2}, {"text": "End-stage right knee osteoarthritis with bone-on-bone changes and functional limitation despite NSAIDs, injections and physical therapy.", "section": "INDICATIONS", "line_end": 5, "line_start": 5}, {"text": "Tricompartmental cartilage loss; components seated and stable through full range of motion.", "section": "FINDINGS", "line_end": 6, "line_start": 6}], "rule_justification": "Documentation explicitly states 'primary osteoarthritis, right knee' with no mention of post-traumatic or secondary etiology; M17.11 is the billable lateralized code.", "guideline_citations": [{"text": "For osteoarthritis, code primary (M17.1x) unless post-traumatic or secondary is documented; honor the global surgical package and do not unbundle.", "source": "Orthopedics Coding Guidance", "section": "Procedures"}]}, {"code": "27447", "role": "procedure", "sequence": 1, "modifiers": ["RT"], "_agreement": 1.0, "confidence": 1.0, "code_system": "CPT", "description": "Arthroplasty, knee, condyle and plateau; medial AND lateral compartments (total knee)", "chart_citations": [{"text": "Total knee arthroplasty, right — replacement of the medial AND lateral femoral condyles and tibial plateau with a cemented prosthesis.", 