, "notes": "1. CPT 70551 with modifier 26: Documentation clearly supports MRI brain without IV contrast. Modifier 26 appended per radiology specialty rules for professional component (radiologist's interpretation). High confidence (0.98).\\n\\n2. ICD-10-CM for headache: The chart documents \\"chronic daily headaches for three months\\" as the indication. The imaging was normal with no structural cause identified. Per radiology coding rules, when no definitive diagnosis is established, code the sign/symptom. The appropriate code would be R51.9 (Headache, unspecified) or potentially G44.209 (Tension-type headache, unspecified, not intractable) for chronic daily headache. However, NEITHER of these codes appears in the candidate ICD-10-CM list provided. The candidate list contains only unrelated chronic conditions (otitis media, sinusitis, COPD, CKD). \\n\\nDOCUMENTATION GAP: The most accurate billable diagnosis code for this encounter (R51.9 or a more specific headache code from G44.x series) is not available in the reference set. I have included R51.9 in the output as it is the standard code for headache symptoms, but note this represents a limitation of the provided candidate codes. Confidence is reduced to 0.75 due to this mismatch.\\n\\nAVOIDED OVERCODING: Did not code any of the unrelated chronic conditions in the candidate list (H65.23, J32.9, J44.1, N18.3) as none are documented or supported by the chart. Did not append RT/LT modifiers as brain imaging is midline/bilateral. Did not code contrast agent (A9579, Q9967) as no contrast was administered.", "stage": "3_coding", "title": "Code Candidate Generation", "samples": 1, "candidates": [{"code": "70551", "role": "procedure", "sequence": 1, "modifiers": ["26"], "_agreement": 1.0, "confidence": 0.98, "code_system": "CPT", "description": "MRI, brain; without contrast", "chart_citations": [{"text": "EXAM: MRI brain without contrast.", "section": "EXAM", "line_end": 2, "line_start": 2}, {"text": "TECHNIQUE: Multiplan