: "Annual wellness visit; includes a personalized prevention plan of service, initial visit"}, {"code": "71045", "source": "DEMO_PLACEHOLDER", "modality": "XR", "description": "Radiologic exam, chest; single view"}, {"code": "71046", "source": "DEMO_PLACEHOLDER", "modality": "XR", "description": "Radiologic exam, chest; 2 views"}, {"code": "73030", "source": "DEMO_PLACEHOLDER", "modality": "XR", "description": "Radiologic exam, shoulder; 2+ views"}, {"code": "73562", "source": "DEMO_PLACEHOLDER", "modality": "XR", "description": "Radiologic exam, knee; 3 views"}, {"code": "73564", "source": "DEMO_PLACEHOLDER", "modality": "XR", "description": "Radiologic exam, knee; 4 or more views"}, {"code": "73110", "source": "DEMO_PLACEHOLDER", "modality": "XR", "description": "Radiologic exam, wrist; 3+ views"}, {"code": "74018", "source": "DEMO_PLACEHOLDER", "modality": "XR", "description": "Radiologic exam, abdomen; single view"}, {"code": "99213", "source": "DEMO_PLACEHOLDER", "modality": "EM_OFFICE", "description": "Office/outpatient visit, established patient, low MDM"}, {"code": "99214", "source": "DEMO_PLACEHOLDER", "modality": "EM_OFFICE", "description": "Office/outpatient visit, established patient, moderate MDM"}, {"code": "99215", "source": "DEMO_PLACEHOLDER", "modality": "EM_OFFICE", "description": "Office/outpatient visit, established patient, high MDM"}], "guideline_excerpts": [{"text": "Risk-adjustment coding captures every chronic condition that is active and addressed at the encounter with MEAT evidence (Monitored, Evaluated, Assessed, or Treated). Code combination codes to full specificity (diabetes WITH its complication, e.g. E11.42, not E11.9 plus a separate neuropathy code). Do not code historical or resolved conditions as active, and do not infer a diagnosis from medications alone. Conditions must be re-documented each calendar year to risk-adjust. The annual wellness visit is reported with G0438 (initial) or G0439 (subsequent).", "source": "HCC Risk Adjustment Coding Guidance", "section": "Capture"}, {"text": "Code the cardiac procedure documented: a complete transthoracic echocardiogram with Doppler is 93306; a routine 12-lead ECG with interpretation is 93000. Append modifier 26 when only the physician's interpretation is performed at a facility. Code the cardiac diagnosis/indication (e.g., heart failure, valvular disease, arrhythmia); use a sign/symptom when no definitive diagnosis is established.", "source": "Cardiology Coding Guidance", "section": "Procedures"}, {"text": "Code the otolaryngology procedure documented: tonsillectomy with adenoidectomy (<12 yrs) = 42820; bilateral tympanostomy tube insertion = 69436 (append modifier 50 for bilateral); diagnostic nasal endoscopy = 31231; septoplasty = 30520; surgical nasal/sinus endoscopy with polypectomy = 31237. A diagnostic nasal endoscopy is bundled into a same-session surgical sinus endoscopy — do not report both. Code the diagnosis (adenotonsillar hypertrophy J35.3, chronic otitis media with effusion H65.23, deviated nasal septum J34.2) and capture ear laterality.", "source": "ENT/Otolaryngology Coding Guidance", "section": "Procedures"}]}, {"hard": true, "notes": "All chronic conditions have appropriate MEAT documentation for HCC capture. Used combination code E11.42 for diabetes with polyneuropathy per HCC guidelines. Heart failure coded as I50.9 (unspecified) as documentation does not specify type (systolic/diastolic/combined) or acuity. CKD stage 3 confirmed with eGFR 48 (30-59 range). No overcoding risks identified.", "stage": "3_coding", "title": "Code Candidate Generation", "samples": 3, "candidates": [{"code": "G0439", "role": "procedure", "sequence": 1, "modifiers": [], "_agreement": 0.667, "confidence": 0.95, "code_system": "CPT", "description": "Annual wellness visit; includes a personalized prevention plan of service, subsequent visit", "chart_citations": [{"text": "ANNUAL WELLNESS VISIT — SUBSEQUENT", "section": "ANNUAL WELLNESS VISIT — SUBSEQUENT", "line_end": 1, "line_start": 1}, {"text": "72-year-old man here for his subsequent annual wellness visit. No new complaints. Health risk assessment and personalized prevention plan completed and reviewed.", "section": "SUBJECTIVE", "line_end": 2, "line_start": 2}], "rule_justification": "Subsequent AWV documented with health risk assessment and prevention plan completed", "guideline_citations": [{"text": "The annual wellness visit is reported with G0438 (initial) or G0439 (subsequent).", "source": "HCC Risk Adjustment Coding Guidance", "section": "Capture"}]}, {"code": "E11.42", "role": "secondary", "sequence": 2, "modifiers": [], "_agreement": 1.0, "confidence": 0.95, "code_system": "ICD10CM", "description": "Type 2 diabetes mellitus with diabetic polyneuropathy", "chart_citations": [{"text": "1. Type 2 diabetes mellitus with diabetic polyneuropathy — stable; monofilament foot exam performed today, decreased sensation unchanged; A1c 7.1 reviewed; continue metformin.", "section": "ASSESSMENT / PLAN", "line_end": 4, "line_start": 4}], "rule_justification": "Type 2 DM with polyneuropathy has MEAT evidence: monitored (A1c), evaluated (monofilament exam), assessed (stable), treated (metformin)", "guideline_citations": [{"text": "Code combination codes to full specificity (diabetes WITH its complication, e.g. E11.42, not E11.9 plus a separate neuropathy code).", "source": "HCC Risk Adjustment Coding Guidance", "section": "Capture"}]}, {"code": "I50.9", "role": "secondary", "sequence": 3, "modifiers": [], "_agreement": 1.0, "confidence": 0.9, "code_system": "ICD10CM", "description": "Heart failure, unspecified", "chart_citations": [{"text": "2. Congestive heart failure — euvolemic on exam; continue lisinopril and carvedilol; reinforced daily weights and low-sodium diet.", "section": "ASSESSMENT / PLAN", "line_end": 5, "line_start": 5}], "rule_justification": "CHF has MEAT evidence: evaluated (euvolemic on exam), treated (lisinopril, carvedilol), assessed (reinforced di