ular disease, arrhythmia); use a sign/symptom when no definitive diagnosis is established.", "source": "Cardiology Coding Guidance", "section": "Procedures"}, {"text": "Code the otolaryngology procedure documented: tonsillectomy with adenoidectomy (<12 yrs) = 42820; bilateral tympanostomy tube insertion = 69436 (append modifier 50 for bilateral); diagnostic nasal endoscopy = 31231; septoplasty = 30520; surgical nasal/sinus endoscopy with polypectomy = 31237. A diagnostic nasal endoscopy is bundled into a same-session surgical sinus endoscopy — do not report both. Code the diagnosis (adenotonsillar hypertrophy J35.3, chronic otitis media with effusion H65.23, deviated nasal septum J34.2) and capture ear laterality.", "source": "ENT/Otolaryngology Coding Guidance", "section": "Procedures"}]}, {"hard": true, "notes": "All three chronic conditions documented with MEAT evidence for HCC capture. COPD coded as J44.1 to capture the acute exacerbation mentioned (even though now at baseline, the exacerbation occurred last month and is still relevant for risk adjustment). No documentation gaps identified. All conditions appropriately addressed for annual wellness visit.", "stage": "3_coding", "title": "Code Candidate Generation", "samples": 3, "candidates": [{"code": "G0439", "role": "procedure", "sequence": 1, "modifiers": [], "_agreement": 1.0, "confidence": 0.95, "code_system": "CPT", "description": "Annual wellness visit; includes a personalized prevention plan of service, subsequent visit", "chart_citations": [{"text": "ANNUAL WELLNESS VISIT — SUBSEQUENT", "section": "CHIEF_COMPLAINT", "line_end": 1, "line_start": 1}, {"text": "76-year-old woman for her subsequent annual wellness visit. Personalized prevention plan updated; screenings reviewed.", "section": "SUBJECTIVE", "line_end": 2, "line_start": 2}], "rule_justification": "Subsequent AWV clearly documented with personalized prevention plan updated", "guideline_citations": [{"text": "The annual wellness visit is report