 appropriate. Avoided overcoding to a more specific pneumonia code (e.g., lobar, bacterial) without documentation.\\n\\n3. PROCEDURE CODING: CPT 71046 selected for 2-view chest X-ray (PA and lateral) as explicitly documented. Modifier 26 appended assuming this is a facility-based study (typical for radiology reports) where the radiologist is billing only the professional component (interpretation). If this were performed in a physician-owned office with the radiologist owning the equipment, modifier 26 would be omitted for the global service.\\n\\n4. ALTERNATIVE DIAGNOSIS CONSIDERATION: R05.9 (Cough, unspecified) was available but not coded. The radiologist's impression provides a more definitive diagnosis (pneumonia), so per coding guidelines, the sign/symptom (cough) should not be coded when a related definitive diagnosis is established. The cough is integral to the pneumonia presentation.\\n\\n5. MEDICAL NECESSITY: J18.9 is a covered diagnosis for CPT 71046 per Medicare policy (covered dx includes J18). Link is appropriate.\\n\\n6. NO LATERALITY MODIFIER: RT/LT modifiers are not applicable to chest X-rays (bilateral anatomy study), even though the finding is left-sided. Laterality modifiers are used for unilateral extremity studies per radiology rules.", "stage": "3_coding", "title": "Code Candidate Generation", "samples": 1, "candidates": [{"code": "J18.9", "role": "primary", "sequence": 1, "modifiers": [], "_agreement": 1.0, "confidence": 0.85, "code_system": "ICD10CM", "description": "Pneumonia, unspecified organism", "chart_citations": [{"text": "Left lower lobe airspace opacity, compatible with pneumonia in the appropriate clinical setting.", "section": "IMPRESSION", "line_end": 6, "line_start": 6}, {"text": "Patchy opacity in the left lower lobe.", "section": "FINDINGS", "line_end": 5, "line_start": 5}], "rule_justification": "Radiologist impression states 'compatible with pneumonia'; imaging findings support diagnosis; code to J18.9 as organism unspecified