102; punch biopsy = 11104; destruction of a premalignant lesion (actinic keratosis), first lesion = 17000; destruction of benign lesions (e.g., warts), up to 14 = 17110. When a biopsy and a same-lesion destruction/excision are done together, the biopsy is bundled — report only the more extensive service. Code the lesion diagnosis (e.g., actinic keratosis L57.0, basal cell carcinoma C44.91); use 'uncertain behavior' (D48.5) when biopsying before a histologic diagnosis.", "source": "Dermatology Coding Guidance", "section": "Procedures"}, {"text": "Report the anesthesia CPT for the procedure being anesthetized (e.g., 00790 upper-abdomen / lap cholecystectomy, 01402 total knee, 01967 labor epidural) and code the underlying diagnosis. Append the physical-status modifier (P1-P6). Payment is base units + time units (each 15 min); record anesthesia start/stop time.", "source": "Anesthesia Coding Guidance", "section": "Units"}]}, {"hard": true, "notes": "Important coding considerations: 1) The addendum confirms the nodule is benign/granulomatous, but this is from an outside pathology report not included in this chart. Since we're coding the radiology service date (before the addendum), I coded the indications (cough, abnormal X-ray) rather than the final benign diagnosis. 2) Applied modifier 26 for professional component as this is a facility-based radiology read. 3) Did not code the nodule finding itself as there's no specific ICD-10 code in the candidate list for benign lung nodule, and the addendum contradicts the initial \\"suspicious\\" impression.", "stage": "3_coding", "title": "Code Candidate Generation", "samples": 3, "candidates": [{"code": "71260", "role": "procedure", "sequence": 1, "modifiers": ["26"], "_agreement": 1.0, "confidence": 0.95, "code_system": "CPT", "description": "CT, thorax; with contrast", "chart_citations": [{"text": "CT chest with contrast", "section": "EXAM", "line_end": 3, "line_start": 3}, {"text": "Helical CT of the thorax following IV cont