nthesis, bilateral (add-on)"}, {"code": "77066", "source": "DEMO_PLACEHOLDER", "modality": "MG", "description": "Diagnostic mammography, bilateral; including CAD when performed"}, {"code": "77062", "source": "DEMO_PLACEHOLDER", "modality": "MG", "description": "Diagnostic digital breast tomosynthesis, bilateral"}, {"code": "77065", "source": "DEMO_PLACEHOLDER", "modality": "MG", "description": "Diagnostic mammography, unilateral; including CAD when performed"}, {"code": "77061", "source": "DEMO_PLACEHOLDER", "modality": "MG", "description": "Diagnostic digital breast tomosynthesis, unilateral"}], "guideline_excerpts": [{"text": "Screening mammography (77067, bilateral) is for an asymptomatic patient; diagnostic mammography (77065 unilateral, 77066 bilateral) is for a breast sign/symptom or to evaluate an abnormal screening finding. If a screening study converts to diagnostic the same day, report the diagnostic code with the appropriate modifier per payer policy.", "source": "Radiology Coding Guidance", "section": "Mammography"}, {"text": "When a screening study (e.g., screening mammography Z12.31, screening AAA ultrasound) is performed, sequence the screening Z-code as the reason for the exam; report any incidental finding secondarily. Do not replace the screening indication with a finding code.", "source": "Radiology Coding Guidance", "section": "Screening"}, {"text": "Code the cardiac procedure documented: a complete transthoracic echocardiogram with Doppler is 93306; a routine 12-lead ECG with interpretation is 93000. Append modifier 26 when only the physician's interpretation is performed at a facility. Code the cardiac diagnosis/indication (e.g., heart failure, valvular disease, arrhythmia); use a sign/symptom when no definitive diagnosis is established.", "source": "Cardiology Coding Guidance", "section": "Procedures"}, {"text": "Code the OB/GYN service documented: obstetric ultrasound (>=14 weeks, transabdominal) = 76805; colposcopy of the cervix with biopsy = 57454; endometrial biopsy = 58100; IUD insertion = 58300. For routine pregnancy supervision, use Z34.8x by trimester (not an O-code) when uncomplicated. Code cervical dysplasia to specificity (CIN I = N87.0, CIN II = N87.1). When one provider gives antepartum + delivery + postpartum care, use the global obstetric package (e.g., 59400) rather than itemizing visits.", "source": "OB/GYN Coding Guidance", "section": "Procedures"}, {"text": "Report the most extensive endoscopic service performed in a session: colonoscopy with snare polypectomy = 45385; colonoscopy with biopsy = 45380; diagnostic colonoscopy = 45378; EGD with biopsy = 43239; diagnostic EGD = 43235. Do NOT separately report the diagnostic scope (45378/43235) when a therapeutic procedure is done in the same session. Code the finding (e.g., colon polyp K63.5, gastritis K29.70); for a screening colonoscopy that finds a polyp, sequence the screening Z-code first.", "source": "GI Endoscopy Coding Guidance", "section": "Procedures"}]}, {"hard": false, "notes": "This is a straightforward screening mammography case. The patient is asymptomatic and presenting for routine screening, so Z12.31 is the appropriate primary diagnosis. CPT 77067 is the correct code for bilateral screening mammography including CAD. Modifier 26 is appended because this is a radiology report documenting the radiologist's professional interpretation (Dr. R. Kim's read), not the technical component. The study was negative (BI-RADS 1) with scattered fibroglandular density, which is a normal finding and does not require a separate diagnosis code. No overcoding risk: the documentation clearly supports screening (not diagnostic) mammography, bilateral, with two views and CAD as stated. Place of service is assumed to be a facility setting based on standard radiology workflow, justifying the 26 modifier.", "stage": "3_coding", "title": "Code Candidate Generation", "samples": 1, "candidates": [{"code": "Z12.31", "role": "primary", "sequence": 1, "