tely when a combined-phase code exists.", "source": "Radiology Coding Guidance", "section": "ContrastPhases"}, {"text": "'With contrast' requires contrast administered intravascularly, intra-articularly, or intrathecally. Oral and/or rectal contrast alone is coded as 'without contrast'.", "source": "Radiology Coding Guidance", "section": "Contrast"}, {"text": "Code the otolaryngology procedure documented: tonsillectomy with adenoidectomy (<12 yrs) = 42820; bilateral tympanostomy tube insertion = 69436 (append modifier 50 for bilateral); diagnostic nasal endoscopy = 31231; septoplasty = 30520; surgical nasal/sinus endoscopy with polypectomy = 31237. A diagnostic nasal endoscopy is bundled into a same-session surgical sinus endoscopy — do not report both. Code the diagnosis (adenotonsillar hypertrophy J35.3, chronic otitis media with effusion H65.23, deviated nasal septum J34.2) and capture ear laterality.", "source": "ENT/Otolaryngology Coding Guidance", "section": "Procedures"}, {"text": "Risk-adjustment coding captures every chronic condition that is active and addressed at the encounter with MEAT evidence (Monitored, Evaluated, Assessed, or Treated). Code combination codes to full specificity (diabetes WITH its complication, e.g. E11.42, not E11.9 plus a separate neuropathy code). Do not code historical or resolved conditions as active, and do not infer a diagnosis from medications alone. Conditions must be re-documented each calendar year to risk-adjust. The annual wellness visit is reported with G0438 (initial) or G0439 (subsequent).", "source": "HCC Risk Adjustment Coding Guidance", "section": "Capture"}, {"text": "CT angiography (CTA) and MR angiography (MRA) include image post-processing and are coded by region (e.g., CTA chest 71275, CTA head 70496, MRA neck 70547-70549). Do not separately report the non-angiographic CT/MRI of the same region performed solely to create the angiographic dataset.", "source": "Radiology Coding Guidance", "section": "Angiography"}]}, {"hard": false, "notes": "Coding reflects the radiologist's professional interpretation (modifier 26 applied to CPT 70551). The indication is chronic headaches (R51.9); the study was negative for intracranial pathology, so no additional diagnosis codes are warranted. Documentation clearly states \\"without contrast\\" and no intravenous contrast was administered. Place of service is assumed to be facility-based (hospital outpatient or imaging center) per standard radiology workflow; if this were a freestanding physician-owned center performing both technical and professional components, modifier 26 would be omitted. No laterality modifier needed for brain MRI. Confidence is high for both codes given explicit documentation of modality, anatomy, contrast status, and indication.", "stage": "3_coding", "title": "Code Candidate Generation", "samples": 1, "candidates": [{"code": "R51.9", "role": "primary", "sequence": 1, "modifiers": [], "_agreement": 1.0, "confidence": 0.95, "code_system": "ICD10CM", "description": "Headache, unspecified", "chart_citations": [{"text": "44-year-old female with chronic headaches.", "section": "HISTORY", "line_end": 3, "line_start": 3}, {"text": "Headache, no intracranial abnormality.", "section": "IMPRESSION", "line_end": 6, "line_start": 6}], "rule_justification": "Chronic headache documented as indication; no intracranial pathology found, so symptom code R51.9 is appropriate.", "guideline_citations": [{"text": "Link to the ordering indication; if no definitive diagnosis, code the sign/symptom.", "source": "Radiology Coding Guidance", "section": "RADIOLOGY RULES"}, {"text": "MRI brain covered for new neurologic deficit, suspected mass, or persistent headache with red-flag features. Covered dx: R51, G45, I63, R55.", "source": "Medicare", "section": "Medical Necessity"}]}, {"code": "70551", "role": "primary", "sequence": 1, "modifiers": ["26"], "_agreement": 1.0, "confidence": 0.98, "code_system": "CPT", "description": "MRI, brain; wi